                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410405-1267-offence-1 t18410405-name-1452"></join>James Richard Tyler</persName>, well knowing the same to have been stolen; against the Statute, &amp;c.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1453" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1453" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1453" type="surname" value="TYLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1453" type="given" value="JAMES RICHARD"></interp>JAMES RICHARD TYLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a seeds-man, living at New Brixton. I bought 3lbs. of marjoram seed at Mr. Sangston's—I sold 1lb. of it, and lost the other from the seed room—it was in a paper bag—I believe this now produced to be mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1454" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1454" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1454" type="surname" value="LANGSTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1454" type="given" value="ALEXANDER ANDERSON"></interp>ALEXANDER ANDERSON LANGSTON</persName>
                  </hi>. Here is my writing on this bag, the same as there was on the bag I sold to Mr. Tyler, and the name of its seed "knotted marjoram."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1455" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1455" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1455" type="surname" value="DENVER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1455" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD DENVER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a seedsman at Brixton. On the 31st of March, the prisoner came with this seed to sell—I asked him what he wanted for it—he said 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a pound—I had known him as being in the habit of buying seed of me and others—I have always considered him very honest—I had the best opinion, of him—I told him the quantity was of no use to me.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184104050204"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long have you known him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Four or five years—he was an honest, hard working man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1456" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1456" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1456" type="surname" value="WOODWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1456" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WOODWARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 157.) I was sent for and took the prisoner—this is the seed—the prisoner said his wife received it from a person he did not know, and his wife told me she received it from a person who has absconded.</p>
